-- Qwest sets Mueller's base salary at $1.2 million
-- 
-- Mon Aug 13, 2007 8:25am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/08/13/us-qwest-mueller-salary-idUSWNAS165420070813

 

 (Reuters) - Qwest Communications International Inc. ( Q.N ), which on Monday named Edward Mueller its chief executive, said it would pay him an annual base salary of $1.2 million with a target bonus percentage of 200 percent. 

 For 2007, Mueller would receive a guaranteed minimum bonus of about $947,000, the company said in a filing with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission. Mueller's compensation package includes options to buy about 2.08 million shares at $8.37, which is Friday's closing price, and a restricted stock award of 896,000 shares. (Reporting by  Kavita Chandran  in Bangalore)